The paper deals with the challenging domain of visual data (images and videos) and proposes a method for mining maximal-size frequent subgraphs in this domain. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with the theoretical challenges of graph mining in messy data collected from complex real-world situations, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of similarity metrics and hidden node relations, which suggests that it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
